    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, \"calibration drift\"? That's a huge red flag. If the sensor was drifting during the pour, it means the record of the pour itself is unreliable. A 2-inch error in a structural slab isn't \"minor\"—it's a violation of code. If I report this as a sensor error that masked a real deviation, I'll have to issue a Work Stop order immediately to verify the physical slab. Are you sure you want to categorize this as a sensor issue rather than a placement error?",
